\tab Magick Effects: The victim is blinded by a random image from his own mind. The victim may test vs. WP to resist the spell\rquote 
s effect only once, in the first round. A successful test means the spell has no further effect. A failed test means the victim is blinded by the hallucination for the full 1d6+3 rounds of the spell.\par 
\tab Notes: Though less reliable than {\i blinding light}, and affecting only a single victim, {\i hallucination} has the potential of a longer duration, a criti
cal value in a melee with numerous opponents. Opposing spellcasters and missile experts are good targets for this spell.\par 
\tab Creatures of low intelligence or less intelligent humanoids unfamiliar with magick may be frightened by such unnatural and bewildering phenomena. At the GM's discretion, the victim may be required to make a Fear test.\par 
