\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 Mask\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 1 Ritual\par 
Preparation: 1d6+3\par 
Magick Points: 6\par 
Range: Caster\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: Caster\rquote s face\par 
Ingredients: Air sublimates*, pigmented glazes\par 
Resistance: See Magick Effects\par 
\par 
\tab Rationale: Air nodes form a mask over the caster\rquote s face, upon which the caster manifest
s the likeness of another humanoid. The caster directs the nodes to shape and order pigmented glaze particles to simulate the colors and textures of the humanoid to be imitated.\par 
\tab 
Magick Effects: The caster creates a colored, textured magickal mask over his own facial features. The mask may present the appearance of any known or imagined humanoid being. Lips, eyes, and other facial features of the mask move in response to the movem
ents of the caster\rquote s facial features. Since the mask is rehearsed during preparation, the illusion is relatively detailed and persuasive. Maintaining the mask during the ritual\rquote 
s duration does not require caster supervision; other actions may be taken without interrupting the magickal effect. Visual test for faults: Int -20. Remote 
physical test: Int. Touch test: Automatic. Penalty for representing an imagined being or a specific individual the caster has never seen: +30 to the viewer\rquote s visual test for faults.\par 
\tab Notes: Since this spell only creates a facial mask, other features of a humanoid\rquote s head (hair, horns, etc.) must be created with physical trappings, or concealed with cloaks, helms, hats. etc.\par 
\tab Variants: This is a simple, restricted version of the more complicated {\i rehearsed image} ritual (Illusion 2).\par 
