\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 {\*\bkmkstart LINK4}Muddle Mind\tab {\f13 lsn}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 1 Spell\par 
Preparation: None\par 
Magick Points: 4\par 
Range: BMP yards\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: One victim\par 
Ingredients: Deleriants* (1/20 dose)\par 
Resistance: WP\par 
{\*\bkmkend LINK1}{\*\bkmkend LINK3}{\*\bkmkend LINK4}\par 
\tab Rationale: The caster places a temporary block between the victim\rquote s conscious mind and his body, permitting the subconscious mind to direct the body\rquote s activities. Thus the victim\rquote 
s more primitive, animalistic impulses are indulged.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: The victim continues to think clearly, but cannot speak or control his body with his thoughts. His body cheerfully does whatever it would like to do if its mind weren\rquote t always telling it what to do.\par 
\tab If undisturbed and unchallenged, the victim will loaf, sit and chew on his tunic, chase butterflies, or try to get a date with anything of the opposite sex.\par 
\tab If challenged, or physically threatened or attacked, the victim ferociously attacks the challenger, regardless of the challenger's identity or the circumstances.\par 
\tab Background: Traceable to Old Slann; identical to spell still used by primitive Slann of Lustria. Extremely ancient, very popular with High Elves, Dark Elves, and all their successors.\par 
\tab Notes: Equally effective for avoiding direct confrontation and for reducing the odds in small unit fights. Its use by thieves, bandits, and rai
ders is so widespread that precautions against it are routine in urban areas and in military situations. The most commonly purchased defensive charm is the Resist Muddle Mind lesser talisman. Even primitive humanoids are generally aware of the vulnerabilit
y of isolated guards or scouts to this spell.\par 
\par 
\par 
{\v Tom Wylie\par 
}\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 Obscure Details\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 1 Ritual\par 
Preparation: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Magick Points: 2\par 
Range: Touch\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 hours\par 
Area of Effect: One object or surface\par 
Reagents: Air sublimates*, gum arabic\par 
Resistance: None\par 
\par 
\tab Rationale: Air nodes form a clinging, form-fitting shell over the area of effect, obscuring most details of its appearance.\par 
\tab 
Magick Effects: The object or surface affected is covered by a dull grey film which hides the details of the surface it is on. Writing, pictures, and shallow engravings are hidden, and features such as bas-reliefs are reduced to very general shapes. Howev
er, it is still obvious what the object is; {\i obscure details} could be used to hide the password inscription on an enchanted sword, but it would still be obvious it was a sword.\par 
\tab 
Only objects up to one pound per level of the caster, or surfaces up to one square yard per level of the caster, are covered. Objects past this limit may not be affected by this spell; surfaces larger than the limit will be partially covered. The film has
 no effect on combat (e.g., a sword affected by this spell would not be considered magickal).\par 
