Range: BMP yards\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: Special\par 
Reagents: Air Sublimates*\par 
Resistance: None\par 
{\*\bkmkend LINK96}{\*\bkmkend LINK115}\par 
\tab Rationale: A series of air nodes travel between the caster and a point  chosen by him, transmitting the caster\rquote s voice.\par 
\tab 
Magick Effects: The caster projects his voice to some point within the area of effect. The caster must be able to see the point chosen, and there can be no physical obstructions between him and that point (e.g. he could not project his voice through a gla
ss window). The caster says what he wishes at any volume, and his voice is reproduced at the point of effect, rather than originating from him. The point of effect may be moved once per round, at the cost of reducing the spell\rquote 
s duration one round each time it is moved.\par 
\tab Notes: This is essentially a more powerful version of the {\i throw voice} spell (Battle Magick, Level 1).\par 
