\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 Hypnotic Command\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 2 Ritual\par 
Preparation: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Magick Points: 6\par 
Range: BMP yds\par 
Duration: 1d6 hours\par 
Area of Effect: One victim\par 
Reagents: Deleriants* (full dose)\par 
Resistance: WP\par 
\par 
\tab Rationale: The caster implants a command in the unconscious mind of the victim. For the duration of the ritual\rquote s effect, the victim unconsciously but intently attempts to follow the command.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: The caster gives the victim a ten-syllable command.\par 
\tab The victim tests vs. WP to resist the compulsion to obey the command. If successful, the ritual has no further effect, though the victim has resisted the compulsion unconsciously, and is unaware of the mental intrusion.\par 
\tab If the test fails, the ritual takes effect, and the victim unconsciously attempts to follow the command for the duration of the magick effect.\par 
\tab Notes: Because the ritual and its trappings are fairly obtrusive, casting a Hypnotic Command stealthily is very difficult. It is most easily practiced on victims which have been rendered unconscious or unaware by some other means (e.g., {\i deepsleep
} or {\i dimwit} spells, combats stuns, etc.). Sleeping victims are also easy marks, as are prisoners, unsuspecting guests, and characters in adjoining rooms.\par 
 \tab 
If the Hypnotic Command is to perform some action that the victim normally would never do without serious consideration (i.e., kill himself, burn down an orphanage, kiss a dwarf, pay too much for lodgings, etc.), the victim is entitled to a new WP test e
ach time he tries to follow the command. In some cases the victim might deserve a WP test each round, if the command is particularly offensive or dangerous, or if the action is repetitive.\par 
\tab Variant: Variants with longer duration are known, but require exotic substances (known to herbalists or alchemists, but scarce and expensive) which render the victim\rquote 
s mind more susceptible. (GM Note: That is, usually these substances are only available to NPC villains.)\par 
\par 
