\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 Improvised Image\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 2 Spell\par 
Preparation: None\par 
Magick Points: 3\par 
Range: BMP yds\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: 4-by-2-yard frame\par 
Reagents: Air sublimates*, pigmented glazes, air herbal condensers\par 
Resistance: See Magick Effects\par 
\par 
\tab 
Rationale: Air nodes form a thin, rigid, sheet-like opaque frame which radiates light through patterns of pigmented glazes suspended in the nodes, producing the colors and forms of a visual image. Herbal condensers provide limited odor effects, while air 
nodes produce limited sound effects.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: A full-color animated image analogous to a motion picture is manifested on a magickal frame 4x2 yards in area. The frame may not be moved during the spell. Sounds and odors may be produ
ced, but the fidelity of these sensations is poor.\par 
\tab This spell may be cast in two ways: as a supervised illusion, and as a programmed illusion. \par 
\tab The caster may supervise the image during the effect\rquote 
s duration, altering visual, aural, and scent details at will. To supervise the improvised image, the caster must supervise the illusion without interruption for the duration of the effect. During that 
period he may take no other actions, and if interrupted, his supervision of the illusion ends immediately, thou
gh the illusion continues for the rest of the effect duration, displaying whatever images, sounds, and scents it was displaying when the caster was interrupted.\par 
\tab 
The caster may alternatively choose to program the visual, aural, and scent details of the illusion as he casts it. The caster need not supervise the illusion, and may perform other actions without interrupting the illusion effects. The illusion itself wi
ll alter according to the programmed instructions of caster for the duration of the effect. The
 player must describe the visual, aural, and scent details he wishes programmed into the illusion when the spell is cast; thereafter, the GM interprets the player's instructions in judging the round-by-round presentation of the illusion.\par 
\tab Improvised on short notice, an Improvised Image is less detailed and persuasive than a Rehearsed Image. Visual Test: Intelligence. Remote Physical Test: Int +20. Touch Test: Automatic. If programmed: +20 bonus to all Intelligence tests.\par 
\tab A successful test reveals the image
 as illusory, but does not permit the viewer to see through the opaque frame. WS and BS are halved for melee and missile attacks and parries by characters on opposite sides of the image. Casting magick missiles at targets obscured by this image requires a 
successful BS test. The caster, or any other object or being, may pass through the image without interrupting the spell.\par 
\tab Notes: Since this spell does not reliably fool most intelligent observers, it is primarily used when urgency or economy prohibits the casting of the more satisfactory {\i rehearsed image}
 ritual. Fortunately, even if the image fails to fool an observer, it provides some screening protection from melee and missile attacks, and distracts and delays those who test to discern the illusion.\par 
\par 
\par 
