\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 Read Mind\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 2 Ritual\par 
Preparation: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Magick Points: 6\par 
Range: BMP yds\par 
Duration: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: One subject\par 
Reagents: Deleriants (1/10 dose)\par 
Resistance: WP\par 
\par 
\tab Rationale: Caster contacts the subject\rquote s mind and suggests a topic. The subject unconsciously summons up thoughts, impressions, and emotions concerning that topic, which the caster monitors as they cross the subject\rquote s mind.\par 
\tab 
Magick Effects: Each round the subject calls to mind a thought, impression, or emotion concerning the topic suggested by the caster. Typically the response is to bring to mind the most obvious thought, impression, or emotion associated with the suggested 
topic. The response is usually in the form of a short sentence or an image which may include sound, smell, taste, and touch.\par 
\tab If the subject passes a WP test, he is subconsciously resistant to the caster\rquote s suggestion. The subject does not realize his mind has been contacted, but the ritual effect fails.\par 
\tab Notes: Casting a {\i read mind} spell stealthily is somewhat difficult. It is most easily practiced on victims which have been rendered unconscious or unaware by some other means (e.g., {\i deepsleep} or {\i dimwit}
 spells, combats stuns, etc.). Sleeping victims are also easy marks, as are prisoners, unsuspecting guests, and characters in adjoining rooms.\par 
