\pard\plain \s1\qj \f18\fs28 SleepWave\tab {\f13 lsn}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 Discipline/Level: Illusion 4 Spell\par 
Preparation: None\par 
Magick Points: 6\par 
Range: Caster\par 
Duration: 1d6 hours\par 
Area of Effect: BMP yards radius sphere\par 
Ingredients: Deleriants (3 doses), aethyr salts*\par 
Resistance: None/Cool\par 
\par 
\tab 
Rationale: The caster broadcasts a Farsleep compulsion that instantaneously sweeps in a wave out from the caster in an expanding circle to the limits of the caster's range. Those unable to withstand the Farsleep compulsion are overcome with drowsiness, th
en fall into a magickal sleep.\par 
\tab Magick Effect: All man-sized humanoids within BMP yards range of the caster are be affected as with the Battle 1st Level spell {\i farsleep}.\par 
\tab Man-sized humanoids who do nothing during the round the spell is cast but concentrate on resisting the {\i farsleep} compulsion may test vs. Cool to avoid the effects of the spell. Those who fail this Cool test are affected by the spell as follows.
\par 
\tab For three rounds affected subjects are drowsy, but awake. All Initiative, WS, BS, skill, characteristic, and standard tests receive a -40 penalty.\par 
\tab At the end of the third round of effect, the subject may test vs. WP to resist at the GM's discretion (see Notes for the {\i deepsleep} spell). If test is passed, no further ef
fect. If test is failed, subject falls into a deep, magickal sleep, and cannot be roused by normal means (e.g., shaking, loud noises, etc.). Subject awakens if he receives a wound (or if violently affected in some other manner, at GM discretion).\par 
\tab Background: Modern adaptation of Ancient High Elven spell.\par 
\tab Notes: Subjects who are forewarned of the coming SleepWave by a friendly caster, or who anticipate a SleepWave attack, can brace themselves against the Farsleep compulsion, and have a chance to avoid its effects.\par 
\tab Non-humanoids creatures are not affected, because their minds are too dissimilar to humanoid minds.\par 
