\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 {\v \tab [Better check this against the complete list of spells for unanticipated interactions!]\par 
}Discipline/Level: Illusion 4 Ritual\par 
Preparation: 1d6+3 rounds\par 
Magick Points: 6\par 
Range: Caster\par 
Duration: 2d6+6 rounds\par 
Area of Effect: BMP radius sphere\par 
Reagents: Aethyr Salts*, Void Salts*\par 
Resistance: None\par 
\par 
\tab Rationale: The caster projects his spirit along a link between a handheld focus and a remote focus. The caster\rquote 
s spirit then focuses itself into the handheld focus and through a magick connection through the void to the remote focus. At the focus the caster\rquote s spirit extends from the remote focus into the surroundings as th
ough the caster were present at the remote focus.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: The caster may use the Sense Magick skill or spells like {\i detect magick} and {\i perceive spirit}
 with a range of BMP yards from the remote focus; these spells may be used to locate other beings. Once other beings are located in this fashion, spells and rituals can be cast at the location of this remote focus as if the caster were present at the remot
e focus.\par 
\tab This spell {\b does not} permit the caster to view the location of the remote focus with normal senses (sight, hearing, touch, etc.). The caster\rquote s spirit, not the caster\rquote 
s body, is present at the remote focus. The caster must use Sense Magic, {\i detect magick}, {\i perceive spirit}, or other similar spells to perceive the remote location.\par 
\tab Note that the caster\rquote s spirit cannot be in two places at once. When the spirit moves at the location of the remote focus, any magickal effects dependent on the caster's supervision or magickal energy are immediately interrupted and ended. 
\par 
\tab Notes: To activate the magickal 
effect, the caster performs the ritual, then touches his focus to his forehead. At this point, the caster becomes unaware of events at the location of his body and at the location of the remote focus. The caster may continue using his body and mind to cast
 spells and rituals, though they will take effect as though the caster was present at the remote location with the remote focus in his hand.\par 
\tab The caster may use the Sense Magick skill or {\i detect magick} or {\i perceive spirit} spells to view the aethyr at the rem
ote location. Mental spells and rituals which affect a single subject require that the subject be perceived by skill, spell, or ritual, so without using a {\i perceive spirit}
, beings at the remote location cannot be perceived as subjects. However, spells and rituals that affect an area (e.g., {\i sleepwave}, {\i painwave}) may be cast to affect all beings within the spell or ritual\rquote 
s range from the remote focus, regardless of whether the caster has viewed the aethyr of the remote location.\par 
